![fedora27comparison](/uploads/e9a22f849d20c23b06e0f2c77d054542/fedora27comparison.png)

I think the problem is in https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/nautilus/blob/cd75bf1e2cdd6a1d4373f7c6623bcddcab80cbf8/src/nautilus-canvas-container.c#L998 `canvas_set_scroll_region_include_visible_area()` not using the correct unit:

```c
     old_scroll_x = gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_hadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (canvas)));
     old_scroll_y = gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_vadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (canvas)));
```
should be changed to
```c
     old_scroll_x = gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_hadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (canvas)))
                    / canvas->pixels_per_unit;
     old_scroll_y = gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_vadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (canvas)))
                    / canvas->pixels_per_unit;
```

However, I don't understand why we would need to include the old "visible area" in the first place. The old area could be meaningless if the geometry of the window changes.

